Changes from 1.7 to 1.7.1

*General:
- Lowered the permissions granted to new oracle database users created for eZ Publish usage
- do not halt anymore the php script upon fatal cluster file handler errors (as the mysql driver does)

*Bugfixes:
- Fixed bug #14513: oracle connector returns empty arrays on some php setups
- Fixed bug #14579: arrayquery() does not work with a string "column" parameter with oracle
- Fixed bug #14608: oracle driver: error when rolling back transactions if an arrayquery() has been executed after trans start
- Fixed bug #15075: persistent objects on tables not prefixed with ez_ do not work with oracle
- Fixed bug #015462: The db upgrade scripts for oracle do not work on table ezpending_actions
